==Statistics==

GitHub was launched in February 2008<ref>[http://github.com/blog/1-hotkeys-and-wikis First GitHub blog post]</ref>.

In a talk at Yahoo! on 2009-02-24, GitHub team members announced that during the year that GitHub had been online, it accumulated 46,000 public repositories, of which 17,000 in the last month alone. 6,200 repositories have been forked at least once and 4,600 have merged from fork<ref>[http://wiki.dandascalescu.com/essays/pita-threshold The PITA Threshold - GitHub vs. CPAN]</ref>.

